ID: TC_003
Title: Login user with valid data

Priority: High
Severity: Blocker

Preconditions:
* User not logged in
* Permanent test user exists in system (Email: vladTest1@gmail.com,         Password: vladTest1)
* Note: Create this user once manually before first test run

Test Data:
* Email: vladTest1@gmail.com
* Password:  vladTest1

Steps:
1. Navigate to “https://automationexercise.com/login”
2. Verify “Login to your account” section visible

3. Enter email in “Email Address” field (vladTest1@gmail.com)
4. Enter password in “Password” field (vladTest1)
5. Click “Login” button
6. Wait for page navigation
7. Verify URL changed to “https://automationexercise.com/”
8. Verify logged in (username visible in header)
9. Verify username format: "Logged in as Vlad"
10. Click "Logout" button
11. Wait for page navigation
12. Verify URL changed to “https://automationexercise.com/login”
13. Verify logged out (login button visible again)
Expected Result: 
1. Login page displays correctly:
- "Login to your account" section visible
- Email and password fields present
- Login button visible
2. After entering valid credentials and clicking Login:
- Page navigates to homepage
- URL changes to https://automationexercise.com/
- No error messages displayed
3. After successful login:
- Username displayed in header
- Format: "Logged in as Vlad"
- Access to authenticated features
- Logout button visible
4. After clicking Logout:
- User logged out successfully
- Redirect to homepage - "Signup / Login" button visible again
- No authenticated features accessible
5. No errors during entire login/logout flow

Actual Result:

Post-conditions:
* User logged out
* Test user remains in system (not deleted)
* Available for next test run

Status: Not Run

